title: whaddup
body:
i’m ina, i’m 19 and i never fucking learned how to communicate with other fandom members which is why it took me over two years to finally have the guts and make my own dan and phil blog

honestly, i dont have any special talents other than juggling so please dont expect too much from my posts. But i do appreciate phanart and shitposts from oher people a lot so you can bet on me reposting every good thing i find lol

although i am an introvert, i would love to find some new people to talk to as i dont really know any dan and phil fans in my real life. so if you have anything to say to me, please do so :)

i am excited to finally be an active part of the phandom and experience this new chapter of dan and phil’s journey with all of you  and dont have anything else to say other than i wish you all a good day! 🖤

summary: Y'all this year's pride Month is so wild like?
body:
Y'all this year’s pride Month is so wild like?

Dan Howell returned after a year of not uploading with an amazing, 45 minute video, coming out as queer and gay, and Phil also alluded he wasn’t straight in a tweet

Eugene Lee Yang came out as gay in a gorgeously done music video that was so beautifully choreographed and done.

And Elijah Daniel bought Hell, Michigan, and renamed it GAY HELL

Also, Andi Mack is returning on June 21st, with one of the returning episodes being part of the first gay storyline on Disney Channel.

(Side note, Taylor Swift dropped ‘You Need to Calm Down, and verses clearly in support of the LGBTQ+ community, and the video featuring many prominent LGBTQ+ people. But this isn’t as important as the ones above because in the end, it is a move by an ally, and while appreciated, it shouldn’t outshine strides made by members of the actual community or things that are directly relevant to them.)
